body:
Using `system.runTimeout` and `system.runInterval` help as creating time based logic. Let's say i want to send a message every 5 secons.
```js
import { system, world } from "@minecraft/server";

// Executed every X ticks
system.runInterval(()=>{
    world.sendMessage("Message from API!");
}, 5 * 20);

// Executed once
system.runTimeout(()=>{
    world.sendMessage("Once from API!");
}, 7 * 20);
```
